In the fast mode, you are required to enter your wallet password for signature authorization for the first payment. After that, when you are required to make additional payments, all you need to do is to confirm the payment request without entering a password to sign the authorization. The security level of this mode is medium, and it helps to enhance your game playing experience.

In the whitelist mode, you are required to enter your wallet password for signature authorization for the first payment. After that, when you are required to make additional payments, you do not need to do anything else to complete the payment authorization. This is the least secure operation, and it gives you the most smooth gaming experience.

1. By staking TRX, you will gain TRON Power (1 TRX = 1 TP) and Bandwidth/Energy.
2. You will receive %s free Bandwidth every day.

3. You can only stake for yourself in Stake 2.0 but can delegate the gained resources to others. The delegated resources can be reclaimed after the lock-up period, if set. Resources without or passed the lock-up period can be reclaimed anytime.
4. Staked TRX can be unstaked anytime. After the %s-day unstaking period, you can withdraw the unstaked TRX.
5. Upon unstaking, the TRON Power and Bandwidth/Energy obtained from the stake will be deducted from your account.
·Stake TRX to get TP (TRON POWER): stake 1 TRX to get 1 TP, and 1 TP equals 1 vote.
·You can also choose to obtain either Bandwidth or Energy. The amount you get depends on the proportion of the TRX you stake to the amount of staked TRX in the entire network.

·The resource can be unstaked once it has been staked for three days. Different types of resources can be staked in separate categories, but the resource can only be unstaked once all the TRX in the same category are staked for at least three days.
·After unstaking, the obtained TP, Bandwidth (or Energy) or other types of resources will be removed.
·After unstaking, the voted TPs will also be removed. You need to restake TRX to gain TPs so that you can vote again.

"1. Multiple signature functions allow for permission grading, and each permission can correspond to multiple private keys. This makes it possible to achieve multi-person joint control of accounts.
2. Multiple signature includes three privilege levels of Owner, Witness, and Active permission.
3. Owner permission is the highest privilege of the account, used to control the ownership of the user, adjust the privilege structure, and the Owner privilege can also execute all contracts.
4. Witness permission can be used to manage the block nodes by super representatives. Non-witness accounts do not have this permission. The block node after modifying witness permission needs to be reconfigured.
5. Active permission is used to provide a combination of permissions, such as providing a permission to perform only the creation of accounts and transfer functions. Active permission supports no more than 8 combinations.
6. When updating the account permission, 100 TRX is charged."

Every account on TRON enjoys the right to vote, and you can vote for the Super Representatives (SRs) to your own liking. You need TRON Power (TP) to vote. Your amount of TPs depends on how much TRX you have staked.
Unstaking TRX will result in losing the corresponding TPs, and hence your votes with these TPs will become invalid. In this event, you can restake TRX to vote again.

Vote with TPs for the top 127 SRs, and you can get rewards according to their reward distribution ratio. “Estimated APR” is the annual percentage rate of rewards you will get by voting for SRs. You can claim your rewards every 24 hours.
Note: Only your most recent vote will be recorded on the TRON network, which means that every new vote will negate all your previous votes.
You can vote for a maximum of 5 SRs at a time in your Ledger.
